(117,1,"2018-06-07 15:45:09","2018-06-07 15:45:09","\n<h1>Public Buildings</h1>\n<p>Cooper Lace is the first choice for museum curators, architects and historic interior designers seeking authentic lace curtains for window treatments. Since our founding in 2007, we have reproduced existing patterns from documents and photographs, scoured our archives for appropriate patterns, and delivered stock items from dozens of our historic lace curtain designs.</p>\n<p>In 2017, were selected to provide all of the lace curtains for both the Utah and Illinois Governors’ Mansions, each a massive undertaking with many patterns and complex measurements. In both instances, the architects and their clients were delighted with the result.</p>\n	<h3>Governor\'s Mansions furnished by Cooper Lace:</h3>\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Illinois-Gov.-cr.-Eric-Hauman.-USE-THIS-INSTEAD-.jpg\" alt=\"Illinois Government Building\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"2668\" width=\"4000\" title=\"Illinois Gov. cr. Eric Hauman. USE THIS INSTEAD\"  />\n		Illinois Governoer\'s Mansion\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/dreamstimelarge_11870189.jpg\" alt=\"Utah Governor\'s Mansion\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1945\" width=\"2568\" title=\"dreamstimelarge_11870189\"  />\n		Utah Governor\'s Mansion\n<p>Lyndhurst, the finest example of Gothic Revival architecture in the United States, commissioned us to create custom-sized muslin for the entirety of their kitchen area to replace their long-lost window treatments. Dan Cooper was also the consultant for the English Wilton Company and assisted in the selection of carpeting for the stairs and tower.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/dreamstimelarge_102307302-copy.jpg\" alt=\"lyndherst building\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1825\" width=\"2738\" title=\"dreamstimelarge_102307302 copy\"  />\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/IMG-5669.jpg\" alt=\"lyndherst indoor\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"2448\" width=\"2448\" title=\"lyndherst curtains\"  />\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Lynhurst-Carpet.jpg\" alt=\"Lynhurst Carpet\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3264\" width=\"2448\" title=\"Lynhurst Carpet\"  />\n<p>Cooper Lace was enlisted for an archival and weave a massive Neo-Classical pattern to accompany and Ogden Codman interior for one of the pre-eminent privately-owned mansions in Newport, Rhode Island. Asked not to reveal its name publicly, we’ve called it “Astor”. The design has been placed in several notable historic buildings including Utah Governor’s Mansion, Edwards Place in Springfield, Illinois and two films sets.</p>\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Edwards-Place-cr.-Robert-Dyer.png\" alt=\"Edwards Place\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1482\" width=\"2494\" title=\"Edwards Place, cr. Robert Dyer\"  />\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Astor-EPa.jpg\" alt=\"Astor EPA\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"3800\" width=\"1846\" title=\"Astor EPa\"  />\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Newport.jpg\" alt=\"Newport Curtain\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"640\" width=\"480\" title=\"Newport\"  />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At Castle in the Clouds in Moultonborough, New Hampshire, we were specifically chosen to recreate an Arts and Crafts pattern for their windows from a period photograph:</p>\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Castle-in-the-Clouds.jpg\" alt=\"Castle in the clouds\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1788\" width=\"2400\" title=\"Castle in the Clouds\"  />\n						Castle in the Clouds Before/After\n				<img src=\"http://cottagelace.local/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Hotel-Jerome-auberge-resorts.jpg\" alt=\"Hotel Jerome\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"415\" width=\"703\" title=\"Hotel Jerome (auberge resorts)\"  />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Hotel Jerome purchased our Brownstone Lace for their Speakeasy, one of many hotels, restaurants and theme parks seeking us out for our unique collection of historic lace panels.</p>\n	<h3><strong>Some of our other notable installations in dozens of historic sites include:</strong></h3>\n","Public Buildings","","publish","closed","closed","","public-buildings","","","2018-08-24 19:07:36","2018-08-24 19:07:36","",0,"http://cottagelace.local/?page_id=117",0,"page","",0),
