(415,1,"2018-08-19 22:37:46","2018-08-19 22:37:46","The Hunter Rose lace curtain panel was inspired by Viennese fashion at the turn of the 20th century, Dard Hunter created this distinctive square rose paired with a graceful stem, and it has become his most recognizable design. An American pattern, designed concurrently with those of Charles Rennie Mackintosh, Hunter Rose lace curtain’s delicate lines will beautifully accent any style of interior, be it a Craftsman Bungalow, Mission, Prairie Style or Mid-Century Modern home. Available as finished panels, as a lace valance and a table scarf.\r\n\r\n100% Scottish Cotton, finished in Ivory. Custom shortening available.\r\nAvailable in Ivory; custom lengths available.\r\nWoven with a rod pocket and header at the top.","Hunter Rose","The Hunter Rose lace curtain panel was inspired by Viennese fashion at the turn of the 20th century, Dard Hunter created this distinctive square rose paired with a graceful stem, and it has become his most recognizable design. An American pattern, designed concurrently with those of Charles Rennie Mackintosh, Hunter Rose lace curtain’s delicate lines will beautifully accent any style of interior, be it a Craftsman Bungalow, Mission, Prairie Style or Mid-Century Modern home. Available as finished panels, as a lace valance and a table scarf.\r\n\r\n100% Scottish Cotton, finished in Ivory. Custom shortening available.\r\nAvailable in Ivory; custom lengths available.\r\nWoven with a rod pocket and header at the top.","publish","open","closed","","hunter-rose","","","2018-08-23 17:13:17","2018-08-23 17:13:17","",0,"http://cottagelace.local/?post_type=product&#038;p=415",0,"product","",0),
